data.enText: wanting to be in the same situation as sb else; wanting sth that sb else has
Everyone is so envious of her.
They were envious of his success.

data.chText: 他看到了另一个男孩眼里那羡慕的目光。
data.enText: He saw the envious look in the other boy's eyes.

data.chText: 他们看着欧洲同行的成功，羡慕不已。
data.enText: They look enviously at the success of their European counterparts.

ex.chText: 我们大家都很羡慕他的新房子。
ex.enText: We are all envious of his new house.

ex.chText: 嫉妒的目光向艾丽斯投来。
ex.enText: Envious glances were cast at Alice.

synonyms.bx: 指因别人获得了自己本想获得的东西、成就等而产生妒忌、羡慕心理的。

ex.enText: He was jealous of his friend's reputation.

ex.chText: 我的女友说我太爱吃醋。
ex.enText: My girlfriend says I'm too jealous.

synonyms.bx: 指对他人的优点、成就等恼恨不满的，也可用于表示对某人吃醋的。

example: he was never covetous before he met her
jealous of his success and covetous of his possessions

value.def: If you are envious of someone, you want something that they have.

example.ex: I don't think I'm envious of your success...
example.tran: 我想我并不嫉妒你的成功。

example.ex: Do I sound envious? I pity them, actually.
example.tran: 我听起来是嫉妒吗？实际上我是可怜他们。

example.ex: 'You haven't changed,' I am often enviously told.
example.tran: “你没什么变化，”常常有人羡慕地对我说。
